### Hybrid E-Commerce System API Tests 
### You can use this file with the VSCode REST Client extension or import into Postman/Insomnia

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

### 1. Add new product
POST {{baseUrl}}/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Super Ultra Wide Monitor",
  "price": 899.99,
  "stock_quantity": 25,
  "category": "Electronics",
  "details": {
    "description": "A massive 49-inch curved monitor for the ultimate workstation.",
    "images": ["http://example.com/monitor1.jpg"],
    "attributes": {
      "brand": "DisplayCorp",
      "refresh_rate": "144Hz"
    }
  }
}

### 2. View product detail (Assuming ID 51 based on 50 seeded products)
GET {{baseUrl}}/products/51

### 3. Add customer review
POST {{baseUrl}}/products/51/reviews
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": 1,
  "rating": 5,
  "comment": "Absolutely phenomenal screen real estate!"
}

### 4. Place an order (ACID Transaction)
POST {{baseUrl}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": 1,
  "items": [
    {
      "product_id": 51,
      "quantity": 2
    }
  ]
}

### 5. View product detail again to see reduced stock (25 -> 23) and new review
GET {{baseUrl}}/products/51

### 6. User purchase history (Combined with MongoDB Activity logs)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/1/history
